    "title": [
      "[Kraken's Fall, River]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "Framing the cliff, stockade fences and a man-made dam collect the churning waters of the rapidly moving river and pool them into a deep reservoir.  Platforms stretch from the western banks, each fitted with long-armed hooks designed to collect the tumbling and spinning logs that bump up and down within the water.  Long ruts in the muddy track display the history of log removal, while splattered boards across the pathway provide firm footing."
    ],
